	<p class="cs709C557D"><span class="cs8498B7A6">&nbsp;WEST VIRGINIA LEGISLATURE</span></p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span><div style="width:49pt;height:32pt;border-width:0.5pt;border-style:solid;border-color:Black;background-color:#FFFFFF;margin:0pt 9pt 0pt 9pt;padding:5pt 0pt 0pt 0pt;">
		<p class="csAC81313F"><span class="csB9803513">FISCAL NOTE</span></p></div>
	</p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4925</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Anders, White, Foggin, Kump, Dillon, and Horst</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced January 29, 2026; referred to the Committee on Government Organization then Health and Human Resources]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, by adding a new article, designated &sect;19-40-1, &sect;19-40-2, &sect;19-40-3, &sect;19-40-4, &sect;19-40-5, &sect;19-40-6, &sect;19-40-7, &sect;19-40-8, &sect;19-40-9, &sect;19-40-10, &sect;19-40-11, and &sect;19-40-12, all relating to the creation of the West Virginia PRIME Act; providing for legislative findings; setting forth definitions; creating authorization of intrastate sale and distribution; providing requirements for custom-exempt facilities; setting forth labeling requirements; creating limitation on regulatory authority; providing for local preemption; setting forth civil liability; providing for intrastate commerce; federal preemption inapplicable; establishing rules; and providing for an effective date.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs456817A0">ARTICLE 40. WEST VIRGINIA PRIME ACT.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-1. Short Title.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall be known and may be cited as the &quot;West Virginia PRIME Act&quot; (Producer&ndash;Retailer Intra-State Meat Exemption Act).</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-2. Legislative Findings.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) The Legislature finds that:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) West Virginia farmers, ranchers, homesteaders, and small processors face significant barriers due to federal and state inspection requirements that exceed what is necessary for safe, voluntary commerce conducted solely within the State of West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) The lack of accessible processing options has created supply bottlenecks, increased costs for consumers, and forced the export of West Virginia livestock to out-of-state or federally controlled facilities.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) The Tenth Amendment reserves to the states the authority to regulate commerce wholly within their borders.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Consumers have the right to voluntarily purchase food directly from local producers, and producers have the right to provide it, provided the transaction is transparent and the product remains within the state.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) The PRIME Act enhances food freedom, strengthens local agriculture, supports rural economies, and promotes self-reliance consistent with West Virginia&rsquo;s agricultural heritage.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Therefore, the Legislature declares that custom-slaughtered meat may be sold, transferred, or distributed within the State of West Virginia without federal or state inspection, subject only to the requirements and limitations of this article.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-3. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">For the purposes of this article, unless the context clearly requires otherwise:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) &quot;Custom-slaughtered meat&quot; means beef, pork, lamb, goat, or other livestock slaughtered and processed in a custom-exempt facility for human consumption.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) &quot;Custom-exempt facility&quot; means a slaughter or processing operation that is exempt from continuous federal inspection under 21 U.S.C. &sect; 623 and operates in compliance with federal custom-exempt standards.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) &quot;Intrastate commerce&quot; means any sale, transfer, distribution, or other transaction that occurs entirely within the borders of the State of West Virginia and is not part of interstate commerce.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) &quot;Producer&quot; means any individual, farm, ranch, homestead, business, cooperative, or agricultural operation that owns livestock for the purpose of sale or processing.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5) &quot;Retailer&quot; means any business selling or serving meat directly to the end consumer, including restaurants, grocery stores, hotels, institutions, schools, and caterers.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(6) &quot;Consumer&quot; means an individual purchasing meat for personal, household, or private use.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(7) &quot;WVDA&quot; means the West Virginia Department of Agriculture.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-4. Authorization of Intrastate Sale and Distribution.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A producer may sell, transfer, or otherwise distribute custom-slaughtered meat directly to a consumer, retailer, restaurant, hotel, grocery, institution, or any other purchaser located within West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) A retailer or restaurant may purchase, store, cook, serve, or sell custom-slaughtered meat to the end consumer.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) Custom-slaughtered meat may not enter interstate commerce.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(d) All transactions under this article are lawful and do not require USDA inspection or participation in state inspection programs.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-5. Requirements for Custom-Exempt Facilities.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A custom-exempt facility participating in intrastate commerce under this article shall:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Maintain federal custom-exempt status;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Keep records identifying the source of livestock and the recipients of processed meat;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Comply with applicable federal sanitation and hazard-control standards for custom operations.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) WVDA may require only minimal registration necessary to maintain a directory of participating facilities.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-6. Labeling Requirements.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) All custom-slaughtered meat sold under this article shall bear the following statement in a clearly legible form:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">&quot;Processed in a custom-exempt facility. Not for interstate commerce.&quot;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) WVDA may not mandate additional labeling, inspection stamps, or regulatory disclosures.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-7. Limitation on Regulatory Authority.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) WVDA may not:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Require inspection of custom-slaughtered meat sold under this article;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Impose any regulation inconsistent with this article;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Restrict the sale, transfer, or distribution of custom-slaughtered meat in intrastate commerce;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(4) Adopt rules exceeding federal custom-exempt facility requirements.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Nothing in this article limits WVDA&rsquo;s authority to respond to documented food-safety emergencies involving a specific, identifiable threat.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-8. Local Preemption.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Counties, municipalities, health departments, or any other political subdivisions may not prohibit or restrict the sale, serving, distribution, or processing of custom-slaughtered meat under this article.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) A local governmental body may act only when:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) A specific and documented imminent public health threat exists; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) The action taken is temporary, narrow, and reported to the Legislature within 30 days.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-9. Civil Liability.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) A producer or custom-exempt facility is not liable for claims arising from the consumption of custom-slaughtered meat when:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) The consumer, retailer, or purchaser voluntarily obtained the product; and</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) The required label under &sect;19-40-6 of this code was provided.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) Nothing in this article protects producers or processors from claims involving gross negligence, reckless misconduct, or intentional harm.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-10. Intrastate Commerce; Federal Preemption Inapplicable.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(a) Meat processed and sold under this article is exclusively intrastate commerce.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(b) No federal law may be interpreted to preempt the operation of this article within West Virginia.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(c) This article shall be construed to the maximum extent permitted under the U.S. Constitution and the Constitution of West Virginia.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-11. Rules.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">WVDA may promulgate rules consistent with this article only if they:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(1) Do not impose inspection requirements;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(2) Do not increase regulatory burdens on custom-exempt facilities or producers;</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(3) Are strictly limited to recordkeeping and labeling already required by this article.</span></p><h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csF3C8A5A3">&sect;19-40-12. Effective Date.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">This article shall take effect on July 1, 2026.</span></p><p class="cs7F45F1B"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to create the West Virginia PRIME Act.</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


